INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install
    make clean

REQUIREMENTS & DEPENDENCIES

    * Apache 2.2 and above
    * mod_perl2

CPAN NOTES

Run command first:

  cpan

Please answer to question as:

    What approach do you want? (Choose 'local::lib', 'sudo' or 'manual')
    [local::lib] sudo

INSTALLATION ON UBUNTU 16.04 AND ABOVE

    apt update
    apt upgrade
    apt-get install apache2 apache2-dev libapache2-mod-perl2 libapache2-mod-perl2-dev
    apt-get install libclass-c3-adopt-next-perl libconfig-general-perl \
      libdbi-perl libfile-copy-recursive-perl libjson-xs-perl libmro-compat-perl \
      libtest-simple-perl libtext-simpletable-perl libtry-tiny-perl liburi-perl \
      libyaml-libyaml-perl libcgi-pm-perl libapache-dbi-perl \
      libtemplate-perl libemail-mime-encodings-perl
    cpan install MPMinus

INSTALLATION ON CENTOS LINUX 7.5 AND ABOVE

  yum update
    yum install epel-release mod_perl mod_perl-devel
    yum install perl-CPAN perl-Config-General perl-Encode perl-DBI \
      perl-CGI perl-Digest-MD5 perl-ExtUtils-MakeMaker perl-ExtUtils-Manifest \
    perl-File-Copy-Recursive perl-File-Temp perl-JSON-XS perl-MRO-Compat \
    perl-PathTools perl-Perl-OSType perl-Template-Toolkit perl-Test-Simple \
    perl-Time-HiRes perl-Try-Tiny perl-URI perl-YAML
  cpan install MPMinus
